spec: socket_extra176
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(socket)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html — Python socket module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Modules/socketmodule.c"
    - "socket_extra175.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.socket class identity: socket.socket.__name__=='socket'; socket.socket.__module__=='socket'; socket.socket.__doc__ startswith checks; socket.socket.__mro__.__len__()==2 (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra174.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.__name__/__package__/__spec__/__loader__/__doc__ module-level identity (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra173.zspec.zsdl — covers socket module function name lengths and comparisons (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra.zspec.zsdl — covers create_connection/create_server/setdefaulttimeout/htons/ntohs names; inet_aton broadcast; inet_ntoa vectors; htons/ntohs/ntohl zero; htonl(1)==16777216 (table + invariants)."
    - "socket.zspec / early extras — cover socket constants AF_INET/AF_INET6; SOCK_STREAM/SOCK_DGRAM; IPPROTO_IP/TCP/UDP; gethostname/getdefaulttimeout names (base spec)."
  notes:
    - "This spec does NOT duplicate invariants present in socket_extra93 through socket_extra175."
    - "Wave 355 theme: socket.socket instance method names — socket.socket.bind.__name__=='bind' (len=4); socket.socket.listen.__name__=='listen' (len=6); socket.socket.accept.__name__=='accept' (len=6; tied with listen); socket.socket.connect.__name__=='connect' (len=7); socket.socket.send.__name__=='send' (len=4; tied with bind); socket.socket.recv.__name__=='recv' (len=4; tied with bind and send); socket.socket.close.__name__=='close' (len=5); socket.socket.setsockopt.__name__=='setsockopt' (len=10); socket.socket.getsockopt.__name__=='getsockopt' (len=10; tied with setsockopt). These anchor the __name__ identity attributes of socket.socket methods as novel content under socketmethods176."
    - "socket.socket.bind.__name__ == 'bind'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. bind is the method to bind a socket to an address; __name__=='bind' (4 chars)."
    - "socket.socket.listen.__name__ == 'listen'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. listen enables a server to accept connections; __name__=='listen' (6 chars)."
    - "socket.socket.accept.__name__ == 'accept'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. accept waits for and returns a new connection; __name__=='accept' (6 chars; tied with listen)."
    - "socket.socket.connect.__name__ == 'connect'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. connect initiates a connection to a remote socket; __name__=='connect' (7 chars)."
    - "socket.socket.send.__name__ == 'send'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. send transmits data on the socket; __name__=='send' (4 chars; tied with bind)."
    - "socket.socket.recv.__name__ == 'recv'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. recv receives data from the socket; __name__=='recv' (4 chars; 3-way tie with bind and send)."
    - "socket.socket.close.__name__ == 'close'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. close closes the socket; __name__=='close' (5 chars)."
    - "socket.socket.setsockopt.__name__ == 'setsockopt'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. setsockopt sets a socket option; __name__=='setsockopt' (10 chars; longest in spec)."
    - "socket.socket.getsockopt.__name__ == 'getsockopt'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. getsockopt gets a socket option; __name__=='getsockopt' (10 chars; tied with setsockopt)."
    - "Note: bind(4)==send(4)==recv(4). 3-way tie at 4 chars: bind, send, recv all have 4-char method names."
    - "Note: listen(6)==accept(6). 2-way tie at 6 chars: listen and accept share the same name length."
    - "Note: setsockopt(10)==getsockopt(10). 2-way tie at 10 chars: setsockopt and getsockopt share the same name length."
    - "Note: full length ordering: bind(4)==send(4)==recv(4) < close(5) < listen(6)==accept(6) < connect(7) < setsockopt(10)==getsockopt(10)."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

